.TH "kstrdup_const" 9 "kstrdup_const" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kstrdup_const \- conditionally duplicate an existing const string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" kstrdup_const
.BI "(const char *s "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
the string to duplicate
.IP "gfp" 12
the GFP mask used in the \fBkmalloc\fP call when allocating memory
.SH "NOTE"
Strings allocated by kstrdup_const should be freed by kfree_const and
must not be passed to \fBkrealloc\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
source string if it is in .rodata section otherwise
fallback to kstrdup.
